docs.snippet: The internet filters that keep foreign companies out have created an environment that pens China’s tech firms inside their home country.

headline.main: Chinese Tech Firms Forced to Choose Market: Home or Everywhere Else

docs.abstract: China's attempts to keep out foreign tech firms has hurt its own start-ups; big, innovative firms like Alibaba and Baidu are penned in, relying almost entirely on domestic business, and music social app Musical.ly has ignored its home market of 700 million internet users to try to flourish in United States.
